data.current_description:
An OpenID Connect Session Management iframe to facilitate e.g. single sign-on or remote logouts.

The iframe implements the OIDC postMessage-based [change notification protocol](http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-session-1_0.html#ChangeNotification) via which a client can receive notifications about session state changes.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve OpenID Connect session management iframe
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves an OpenID Connect Session Management iframe for monitoring session state changes. This endpoint returns an HTML iframe that implements the OIDC postMessage-based change notification protocol, enabling clients to receive real-time notifications about session state changes (e.g., user logout, session expiration). Requires the client_id parameter. Integrate the returned iframe into your application to support single sign-on and remote logout scenarios. The iframe communicates session state changes via postMessage events.
data.reasoning: Original summary 'Include a session iframe' is vague and doesn't clarify that this retrieves/returns an iframe. data.current_description:
Start a session with Authentiq Connect to authenticate a user.

```
GET https://connect.authentiq.io/authorize?client_id=<your-client-id>&response_type=code+id_token&scope=openid+email&redirect_uri=<your-redirect-uri>&state=0123456789
```

This endpoint also supports the POST method.
data.description_suggestion: Initiates an OAuth 2.0 authorization request to authenticate an end-user. Accepts authorization parameters including client_id, response_type, scope, redirect_uri, and state. Supports both GET and POST methods. On successful authentication, redirects to the specified redirect_uri with authorization code and/or ID token in the response. Requires valid client registration and matching redirect_uri.

data.description_suggestion: Exchanges an authorization code for an ID Token and/or Access Token as part of the OAuth 2.0 authorization code flow. data.current_description:
An OpenID Connect Session Management iframe to facilitate e.g. single sign-on or remote logouts.

The iframe implements the OIDC postMessage-based [change notification protocol](http://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-session-1_0.html#ChangeNotification) via which a client can receive notifications about session state changes.
data.summary_suggestion: Retrieve OpenID Connect session management iframe
data.description_suggestion: Retrieves an OpenID Connect Session Management iframe for monitoring session state changes. This endpoint returns an HTML iframe that implements the OIDC postMessage-based change notification protocol, enabling clients to receive real-time notifications about session state changes (e.g., user logout, session expiration). Requires the client_id parameter. Integrate the returned iframe into your application to support single sign-on and remote logout scenarios. The iframe communicates session state changes via postMessage events.
